You've now built every component of a modern transformer architecture from scratch:

| Notebook | What you built |
|----------|---------------|
| **00–10** | Complete GPT-2 style transformer (v1) |
| **11: RoPE & RMSNorm** | Modern normalization and position encoding |
| **12: Modern Attention** | GQA, QK normalization, sliding window attention |
| **13: Modern Transformer** | ReLU², value embeddings, residual scaling, softcapping |

The full symbol table you've learned:

| Notebook | Symbols |
|----------|---------|
| 00 | Σ (sum), xᵢ (indexing) |
| 01 | W ∈ ℝ^{m×n} (matrix shape), W[i] (row lookup) |
| 02 | μ (mean), σ² (variance), ε (epsilon), γ/β (learnable scale/shift) |
| 03 | Q, K, V (projections), d_k (head dim), softmax, ^T (transpose) |
| 04 | GELU, Φ (Gaussian CDF), erf (error function) |
| 05 | x_{l+1} = x_l + F(x_l) (residual connection) |
| 06 | W_E^T (transposed weight tying) |
| 07 | L (loss), log, P(y\|x) (conditional probability) |
| 08 | α (learning rate), β₁/β₂ (decay rates), ∇ (gradient), θ (parameters) |
| 09 | ∇_θ L (gradient of loss w.r.t. params) |
| 10 | T (temperature), P(i) = exp(zᵢ/T) / Σⱼ exp(zⱼ/T) |
| 11 | RMS(x), θᵢ (RoPE frequency), R(θ) (rotation matrix) |
| 12 | n_h, n_kv (head counts), w (window size), W_Q/W_K/W_V (separate projections) |
| 13 | ReLU²(x), λ_r/λ_0 (residual scaling), softcap(x), W_E/W_H (untied weights) |

Every symbol maps directly to Nx code you wrote. You can now read modern ML papers and understand the architecture behind LLaMA, Gemma, and similar models.

## Key Concepts

| Concept | What it means |
|---------|--------------|
| **ReLU²** | `max(0, x)²` — sparser activations than GELU, better feature selection |
| **Value embeddings** | Learned token signals added to V on alternating layers |
| **Residual scaling** | `λ_r · x + λ_0 · x₀` — per-layer control of information flow |
| **x₀ skip** | Direct connection from initial embeddings to every layer |
| **Logit softcapping** | `c · tanh(logits/c)` — prevents extreme confidence, bounds outputs to [-c, c] |
| **Untied embeddings** | Separate input (wte) and output (lm_head) weight matrices |
| **Bias-free** | No bias in any linear layer — fewer params, RMSNorm handles normalization |
